personalInfo.education: University of South Carolina-Aiken (2013, Business Management)
personalInfo.splInterest: Fellowship with his friends, ping pong, basketball, football, pool and cornhole

tourBios.exmtStatus: Finished T14 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.curYearHigh: Opened the Club Colombia Championship with a 2-over 73. After a 67 in the second round found himself seven off the pace. Fought his way into contention with a third-round 65. Continued to climb the leaderboard with an final-nine 33 to place at 11-under par. Missed a six-foot birdie try on the par-5 finishing hole to get to 12-under and finished T2 with Richy Werenski. Waited around in the scoring trailer to congratulate Sebastian Munoz on his victory after Munoz signed his card.
tourBios.carHigh:
From 2013 to 2015 played on the eGolf Tour and NGA Tour/Swingthought Tour, winning the Carolina Pro Series event at Brunswick Plantation in 2013, defeating Joe Young by two shots.

2015: Played in 17 Web.com Tour events, making three cuts, with his best finish a T35 at the United Leasing Championship in May.

 2014: Was medalist by three shots at a second-stage Qualifying Tournament event at Brooksville, Fla...Finished T43 at Q-School Finals in December.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Named Apollo High's 2008-09 Wendy's High School Heisman winner...Earned Division II All-American honors in 2012 and 2013 at U. of South Carolina-Aiken...Voted Peach Belt Conference Player of the Year in 2013.
tourBios.personal: Graduated from Apollo High School in Owensboro, Ky. in 2009...Earliest golf memory was playing with his dad for the first time, hitting a tee shot down the middle of the fairway and chasing after it to hit the next shot...Turned to golf knowing "every time you walk off the course you feel like you could have done better at something."...Favorite course is Palmetto GC in Aiken, S.C...Favorite athletes are Steph Curry, Tim Tebow and LeBron James...Favorite pro teams are those that play in Philadelphia...Favorite TV shows are "NCIS," "NCIS-LA," "Blindspot" and "Quantico."...Other favorites include Chick Fil A for breakfast, "chick flicks" and heart-warming movies, desserts, The Bible and Charleston, S.C...Playing in the Masters Tournament and getting to play Pine Valley and Augusta National are at the top of his bucket list...Motto is "We're far worse than we ever imagined, and for more loved than we could ever dream." ...Twitter handle is @MattAtkinsUSCA.
